comments.body:
This is a basic implementation of the Luhn algorithm for computing the checksum (14th digit):
```
def compute_barcode_checksum(barcode_without_checksum)
  is_odd = true
  sum_total = 0
  while barcode_without_checksum > 0 do
    last_digit = barcode_without_checksum % 10
    #odd digits get multiplied by 2 and summed
    #if product is => 10, subtract 9
    if is_odd
    then
      do_odd = last_digit * 2
      sum_total =
        if do_odd < 10
        then sum_total + do_odd
        else sum_total + (do_odd - 9)
        end
    # if even, add to sum
    else sum_total = sum_total + last_digit
    end
    is_odd = not(is_odd)
    # integer divide over 10 to move on to the next digit
    barcode_without_checksum = barcode_without_checksum / 10
  end
  remainder = sum_total % 10
  if remainder == 0
  then return remainder
  else return 10 - remainder
  end
end
```
@regineheberlein Is this the same algorithm as https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/values/barcode.rb ?
